in</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":2,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":47,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Philip Tilney was born about 1335, in Boston, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Sir Frederick Tilney, was 31 and his mother, Margery Lyne, was 28. He had at least 2 sons with Grace Rosse. He died in 1394, in England, at the age of 60, and was buried in Boston, Lincolnshire, England."},"et":{"Abt 1335–1394":"umbes 1335–1394","1335–1394":"1335–1394","1338–1405":"1338–1405","1367–1406":"1367–1406","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1305–1360":"1305–1360","1309–1336":"1309–1336","Abt 1335":"umbes 1335","1394":"1394","1360":"1360","Abt 1367":"umbes 1367","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1305":"1305","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1335":"1335","1367":"1367","about 1336":"umbes 1336","1453":"1453","ABT    1370":"umbes 1370","1309":"1309","1406":"1406","1405":"1405","Of,Boston,Lincolnshire,England":"Boston, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Boston, Lincolnshire, England, United K